Overview
Build a mock but fully functional web banking app for “Hellenic Bank” with persistent data, modern UI, and essential banking feature CRUD. The app comprises Admin and User roles with Spring Boot + Spring Security backend, MySQL persistence, and React (Vite) frontend using Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui. Core services: Accounts, Transfers, Cards, Loans, and a Budgeting Dashboard. Include navbar with provided lettered logo and favicon without letters. Focus on correctness, data integrity, role-based access control, and testable defaults.

Target Audience
- Programming Students: building and demonstrating a full-stack banking MVP for a final exam.
- Instructors/Reviewers: verifying role-based security, CRUD correctness, and UX completeness.
- QA/Peers: validating data persistence and responsiveness.

Core Features
1) Implement Authentication & Authorization
- Roles: ADMIN, USER
- Functions:
  - Register (User only) and Login
  - JWT-based auth; password hashing (BCrypt)
  - Protect routes via Spring Security and React route guards
- Acceptance:
  - Unauthenticated users can only access Login/Register, Public Home
  - ADMIN can access Admin Dashboard and all CRUD on all entities
  - USER can only access own resources (accounts, cards, transfers, loans)
  - Tokens stored in httpOnly cookies or secure local storage with refresh flow (prefer httpOnly cookie)

2) Manage Accounts (CRUD)
- Fields: id, userId, type [CHECKING, SAVINGS], iban, balance, currency (EUR), status [ACTIVE, FROZEN], createdAt
- Functions:
  - ADMIN: full CRUD
  - USER: Read own, Create request (optionally approved automatically in MVP), Update limited (nickname/type), Delete disabled for USER (soft close request optional)
- Acceptance:
  - Create/Read/Update work with validation (unique IBAN), balance non-negative
  - Filtering by userId and status

3) Execute Transfers (Create + Read)
- Fields: id, fromAccountId, toIban, amount, currency, description, status [PENDING, COMPLETED, FAILED], createdAt
- Functions:
  - USER: Create transfer from owned account; list own transfers
  - ADMIN: Read all, update status, revert (MVP: manual admin action/set status)
- Acceptance:
  - Amount > 0 and <= available balance
  - On COMPLETED: deduct from source balance; log transaction; idempotency via client-generated requestId (optional)
  - Prevent transfers from frozen accounts

4) Manage Cards (CRUD)
- Fields: id, userId, accountId, type [DEBIT, CREDIT], maskedNumber, expiryMonth, expiryYear, status [ACTIVE, BLOCKED], limit (for CREDIT), createdAt
- Functions:
  - ADMIN: full CRUD
  - USER: Read own, Create for owned account, Update status (block/unblock), Delete own (soft delete allowed)
- Acceptance:
  - Mask card number display (e.g., **** **** **** 1234)
  - Enforce account ownership

5) Manage Loans (CRUD)
- Fields: id, userId, principal, interestRate, termMonths, status [PENDING, APPROVED, REJECTED, ACTIVE, PAID], monthlyPayment, createdAt
- Functions:
  - USER: Create application; Read; Update allowed only when PENDING (cancel)
  - ADMIN: Approve/Reject; Activate; Mark PAID; Edit terms before activation
- Acceptance:
  - Monthly payment calculated on approval/activation
  - Integrity checks: principal > 0, interestRate within bounds, termMonths > 0

6) Visualize Budgeting Dashboard
- Widgets:
  - Monthly Spending by Category (derived from transfers with categories)
  - Income vs. Expenses summary
  - Upcoming Bills/Payments (mock)
  - Savings progress (from accounts with type SAVINGS)
- Functions:
  - USER: View only; Categorize transfer (CRUD on categories per transfer)
  - ADMIN: N/A
- Acceptance:
  - Charts render from API; default mock categories if none assigned
  - Filters by month

7) Provide Admin Dashboard
- Tiles:
  - Users count, Accounts, Active Cards, Loans by status, Total Transfers this month
  - Tables with last 10 transfers, pending loans
- Actions:
  - Approve/Reject loans; Change card status; Freeze/Unfreeze accounts
- Acceptance:
  - All actions trigger toast notifications; updates visible without refresh (optimistic or refetch)

8) Ensure Branding & Assets
- Navbar with provided lettered logo; favicon without letters
- Theme: modern “Cluely” vibe; colors: blues and gold accents
- Acceptance:
  - Logo visible at left; favicon set in index.html; responsive across mobile/desktop

User Flows
- Register & Login (User)
  - User registers (email, password, name). On success, auto-login. Redirect to User Dashboard.
- Create Account (User)
  - User navigates Accounts > New Account > Select type > Submit > Account created with generated IBAN.
- Make Transfer (User)
  - User selects source account > enters to-IBAN, amount, category, description > Submit > balance updates and transfer recorded.
- Manage Card (User)
  - User creates debit card for account > views masked number > can block/unblock.
- Apply for Loan (User)
  - User completes form (principal, term) > status PENDING > Admin approves > monthlyPayment calculated > status ACTIVE.
- Review Budget (User)
  - User opens Budgeting Dashboard > sees charts for current month > assigns categories to uncategorized transfers.
- Admin Loan Approval (Admin)
  - Admin Dashboard > Pending Loans table > Approve/Reject > record updates and visible to user.
- Admin Account Control (Admin)
  - Admin Dashboard > Accounts table > Freeze account > prevents transfers.

